                                    <h2>Working with the other staff members</h2>
                                    There are two different staff roles in the server, the <staffrole>@FORTHECONTENT
                                        STAFF</staffrole> role and the <modrole>@FORTHECONTENT MOD</modrole> role.
                                    Usually we refer to all members in both of these roles as staff members, but to
                                    hopefully lessen the confusion when reading this guide, we will be highlighting
                                    any references to members of a specific role in the color associated with the role they are in.
                                    When reffering to all staff members from either role, they will be referred to as 'staff' or 'staff members' neutrally

                                    <br><br>

                                    While moderating, not every scenario is going to be cut and dry and there may be some situations that
                                    aren't covered below. A big part of moderating the server is working with the other
                                    staff members to decide the best course of action to take in those uncommon
                                    situations. If you're unsure about anything, reach out to a <staffrole>staff member</staffrole> and they should be able to help you out

                                    <br><br>

                                    Initially, you will start out in the mod role with the option to be moved to
                                    the staff role after no specific amount of time, and only if it's something you're interested in doing. But for now, the mod role
