                                    <h2>Enabling two-factor authentication (2FA) and developer mode</h2>
                                    <strong>Two-Factor Authentication</strong><br>
                                    To gain access to Discord's built-in moderating features you will need to make sure
                                    you have 2FA enabled on your account. You can enable 2FA by going to your user
                                    settings > my account > and setting up 2FA from there. Unfortunately, if you're
                                    unable to enable 2FA on your account, you won't be able to proceed with your application

                                    <br><br>

                                    <strong>Developer Mode</strong><br>
                                    To use some of 4DC's commands, you will need to enable developer mode on Discord.
                                    This will allow you to access things like user IDs and message IDs. You can
                                    enable developer mode by going to your user settings > advanced > and switching on
                                    developer mode from there

                                    <br><br>

                                    More information about <a href="https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/219576828-Setting-up-Two-Factor-Authentication" target="_blank">setting up 2FA here</a><br>
                                    More information about <a href="https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/206346498-Where-can-I-find-my-User-Server-Message-ID-" target="_blank">developer mode here</a>

                                    <br><br>

