                                    <h2>Deleting messages, timeouts and bans</h2>
                                    All of these actions can be made by right-clicking a user or message, or by
                                    hovering over a message while holding the SHIFT key to bring up the quick
                                    action menu
                                    <br><br>
                                    I'm sure it goes without saying, but please do not abuse these actions. Try to be
                                    reasonable and fair when taking any sort of action against a user. Start at the
                                    least permanent type of action first <i>(message delete, verbal warning, rule command)</i>
                                    and only use more permanent actions <i>(warning, timeout, ban)</i> when necessary, or when taking follow-up actions
                                    <br><br>
                                    When using the warning, timeout and ban actions, please make
                                    sure you include a descriptive reason for doing so. Referencing a specific rule is
                                    generally a good idea as well. This will help other staff understand why certain
                                    actions were taken and if more serious actions needs to be taken later on

                                    <br><br>

                                    <h2>Constructive feedback</h2>
                                    Once in a while, a <staffrole>staff member</staffrole> may message you privately to
                                    let you know if a situation you were moderating could have been handled differently,
                                    or if you might have missed something that should have been moderated. It will be a
                                    little bit of a learning curve at first with the varying amounts of messages and
                                    content being posted daily, as well as the different ways we handle individual
                                    situations, so feedback like this is purely to make sure we're all on the same page
                                    as each other and not because you did anything wrong per se

                                    <br><br>

                                    <h2>Your activeness and attitude as a staff member</h2>
                                    While we don't expect staff to spend more time online then they usually would, we do
                                    expect that they will maintain a certain level of activeness during the time that they are
                                    in a staff role, so that all staff share in the effort of moderating equally. A few examples
                                    of this would be;
                                    <br><br>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            • If a new users joins the server and says hello in chat, welcome them in,
                                            maybe direct them to grab some profile flair from <channel>#self-roles</channel>, and
                                            also be willing to answer any questions they might have regarding the server and
                                            how it works
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            • Expect the fact that a lot of new members may not have read the rules
                                            right away and that they may post something that isn't allowed, give them
                                            the benefit of the doubt, and politely direct them to read the rules before
                                            taking action
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            • If you have a spare minute, take a quick look through all the channels
                                            to see if anything needs to be moderated or if any questions need to be
                                            answered
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            • Answering questions or review requests in the <channel>#help-and-advice
                                            </channel> and <channel>#gfx-video-review</channel> channels. Please keep in
                                            mind that if you are unsure of how to answer a question, or provide helpful
                                            feedback, it is best to let someone else who might have more experience
                                            answer those threads, as the last thing we want to do is provide someone
                                            with
                                            incorrect information or poorly thoughtout feedback
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>

                                    <br>

                                    <h2>Discord's tos and community guidelines</h2>
                                    Following <a href="https://discord.com/terms" target="_blank">Discord's ToS</a> applies to everyone who uses Discord, but on top of that, because FTC is a community server,
                                    we are also required to follow and moderate users based on <a href="https://discord.com/guidelines" target="_blank">Discord's Community Guidelines</a> as well. It's important that you familiarize yourself with these guidelines as not following them and allowing users to break them can result in FTC being terminated 

                                    <br><br>

                                    <h2>Stepping down or being removed from a staff position</h2>
                                    In rare circumstances where we feel like you are not a great fit for the team, you will
                                    be contacted privately and informed that you are being removed from the staff role.
                                    Please don't take this personally. We just want to make sure all staff are on
                                    the same page and that we can all work well with each other, and sometimes people just
                                    aren't the right fit
                                    <br><br>
                                    If at any point you feel like stepping down as staff, you're more than welcome to
                                    reach out to a <staffrole>staff member</staffrole> and let them know
